{"_id":"5qO56lM5zVdndeSg","name":"Walls","content":"<h1>Walls</h1>\n<p> </p>\n<p>Walls can be rendered in 3d, you can chose any texture, transparent or animated. If the texture has transparency you will need to set the wall opacity to less than 1. This is a workaround because setting objects to transparent in 3d makes them more expansive to comupte and since i cannot autodetect t ransparency you will have to set this to 0.99 to enable the transparency in the image.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<h2>Textures</h2>\n<p> </p>\n<p>By default the texture of the wall will be automatically tiled. If you wish to stretch it instead simply enable the option in the wall configuration</p>\n<p>The color option will also apply a tint to the texture, so leave it white to get the original color.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<h2>Doors</h2>\n<p> </p>\n<p>Doors can be interacted with, clicking on a door will trigger the standard foundry interactions. Right click to lock also works.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<h2>Material</h2>\n<p>You can also customize how refletive or rough a wall is</p>","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Cspu3pxFr7tu7SU7":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.dyAW3BUkwfncTIvQ"}}}
{"_id":"7Qfpqoo0Gm3fdUyT","name":"Controls","content":"<h1>Controls</h1>\n<p> </p>\n<h2>Camera Controls:</h2>\n<p> </p>\n<ul>\n<li> <strong>Left mouse + drag</strong> -&gt; Rotate Camera</li>\n<li> <strong>Right mouse + drag</strong> -&gt; Pan Camera</li>\n<li> <strong>Scroll Wheel</strong> -&gt; Zoom Camera</li>\n</ul>\n<p> </p>\n<h2>Token Interaction:</h2>\n<p> </p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Left mouse + drag</strong> -&gt; Drag Move Token \n<ul>\n<li>There is no box multiple selection but if you have multiple tokens selected and move one the others will follow with the same delta of movement/elevation</li>\n<li>While dragging, scroll wheel will change altitude (you can add shift\\ctrl modifiers for granular changes)</li>\n<li>Default +\\-5 elevation, shift +\\-1, control +\\-0.1</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li><strong>Shift + Click</strong> -&gt; Select multiple</li>\n<li><strong>Ctrl + Mouse Wheel </strong>-&gt; Rotate currently controlled tokens</li>\n<li><strong>Ctrl + Click (on empty spot)</strong> -&gt; Deselect all tokens</li>\n<li><strong>F </strong>-&gt; If collision is enabled, hold F while dragging to \"Fly\" and ignore the collision</li>\n</ul>\n<p> </p>\n<p><em>Standard foundry interactions work (Left click to select, right click for HUD, Double left for sheet, Double right for config\\target)</em></p>\n<h2><em>Measured Template</em></h2>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>F </strong>-&gt; When placing moves the second point of the template into free mode allowing to change it's elevation with mouse wheel</li>\n<li><strong>Ctrl + Mouse Wheel </strong>-&gt; After a template is place with a template selected to rotate it</li>\n<li><strong>Mouse Wheel </strong>-&gt; When in template preview (dnd5e when casting a spell) to rotate the template</li>\n</ul>\n<p> </p>\n<h2>Pings</h2>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Shift + Q</strong> -&gt; Ping and move the camera</li>\n<li><strong>Shift + E</strong> -&gt; Ping Location</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Rebinding</h2>\n<p>You can rebind all the controls in the configure controls menu.</p>","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Cspu3pxFr7tu7SU7":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.skKRpoNoqvX3l3kr"}}}
{"_id":"7gl74gQSbZdWdi5h","name":"Fog of War","content":"<h1>Fog of War</h1>\n<p>To create a fog of war box, make a box shaped measured template. In it's configuration you will find a checkbox to set it as fog of war. This box will appear solid black for players, if they try to clip into it with the camera the screen will go black.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<h1>Fog Exploration</h1>\n<p>You can enable the new fog exploration experimental setting in the scene configuration. Keep in mind that this option can be quite hungry on performance.</p>","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Cspu3pxFr7tu7SU7":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.ooZjjkA5TgWMJhTf"}}}
{"_id":"8YdPNAZ4AQX8I7Ew","name":"PBR Materials","content":"<h1>PBR Materials</h1>\n<p>Tokens, walls and the scene table support PBR Materials</p>\n<p>To load a pbr material you need a specific file naming stuctures. The files must be named as follows and be all in the same folder - Example:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Wood077_1K_AmbientOcclusion.jpg</p>\n<p>Wood077_1K_Color.jpg</p>\n<p>Wood077_1K_NormalGL.jpg</p>\n<p>Wood077_1K_Roughness.jpg</p>\n<p>Wood077_1K_Metalness.jpg</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p> </p>\n<p>As you can see all the files share a root name then keywords to differentiate the different textures. You can find materials already setup this way here <a href=\"https://ambientcg.com/list?type=PhotoTexturePBR,AtlasPBR,DecalPBR\">AmbientCG</a></p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>For 3D Canvas to pickup these materials you need to select one of the files in the image field.</p>\n<p><strong>IMPORTANT: For the full material to be loaded you can pick any of the images but NOT Color, otherwise only the color texture will be used</strong></p>\n<p>For walls you can load the image in it's texture field, same for tokens and the scene Table. Tokens also require that the material is set to PBR.</p>\n<p><strong>*Note: For performance reasons displacement maps are not supported</strong></p>","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Cspu3pxFr7tu7SU7":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.hE0ytQrLymsJl6Yg"}}}
{"_id":"8t4nAQ7eDZ6aMLUf","name":"Scene Configuration","content":"<h1>Scene Configuration</h1>\n<p> </p>\n<p>You will get a massive amount of settings but do not worry :)</p>\n<p> </p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Enable 3D on load</strong>: Automatically load the 3d mode when loading the scene</li>\n<li><strong>Skybox image</strong>: The image to be used as skybox, check resources(3d).md for links to where to get them already formatted with the correct names</li>\n<li><strong>Display Table</strong>: Enabling this will create a \"table\" in the area where the padding of your 2d scene is, if you don't set a texture it will be black - i suggest wood textures from forgotten adventures</li>\n<li><strong>Table Texture</strong>: The texture for the table, this texture will be stretched not tiled so use something with a decent resolution</li>\n<li><strong>Fog</strong>: Fog is mostly a performance option, it's NOT Fog of War. Enabling it will hide distant objects in a fog. You can customize the color and the distance- the distance is in canvas pixel units. Keep in mind that enabling the fog will make the skybox not visible.</li>\n<li><strong>Automatic Sun Position</strong>: This setting will attempt to sync the 3d sun with ether world time (if you use small time for example) or the darkenss level of the scene. Disable to configure manually.</li>\n<li><strong>Show Scene Walls</strong>: Renders the scene walls in 3D Keep in mind that to set a custom height for the wall you will need to use the module Wall Height</li>\n<li><strong>Show Scene Floors/Polygons</strong>: Displays tiles on the scene, to set the height of tiles you will need to use the module Levels</li>\n<li><strong>Render scene lights</strong>: Create foundry lights in the 3d environment as well, keep in mind that for performance reasons they will illuminate through objects</li>\n<li><strong>Enable Collision</strong>: If enabled collision calculations for token dragging will be done on this scene. You still need to enable collision plane on terrain tokens, by deafult the scene background is always a collision plane.</li>\n</ul>\n<p> </p>\n<h2>Weather Effects</h2>\n<p>You can enable weather effects in the scene configuration, by using the UI you can combine up to one preset and one custom effect or two presets - with macros you can stack an unlimited amount of presets. </p>\n<p>To stack custom presets, you will need to set a flag on the scene</p>\n<div><code><sup>canvas.scene.setFlag(\"levels-3d-preview\", \"particlePresetCustom\", presetData)</sup></code></div>\n<p>Where presetData is an array of particle effects data objects - please note that this is the RAW data processed by the system and NOT the numbers you set in the scene - to get the raw data simply check the console log when a weather is initialized - the raw data of that effect will be shown in the console.</p>","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Cspu3pxFr7tu7SU7":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.2GchS8V113reCZ0U"}}}
{"name":"Spell Effects / Particle System","content":"<h1>Particle System</h1>\n<p> </p>\n<p>The Particle system is driven by macros - you can find the full documentation <a href=\"https://github.com/theripper93/canvas3dcompendium/blob/master/wiki/ParticleSystem.md\">HERE</a></p>","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Cspu3pxFr7tu7SU7":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.B0Q4jzVjx8a8FOgw"}},"_id":"FSVwDqRdfY3mizV2"}
{"_id":"GyiFBDwFpuK3odsi","name":"Vision & Sight","content":"<h1>Vision &amp; Sight</h1>\n<p> </p>\n<p>While in 3d the whole map will be revealed, token vision is still respected the same way it works in the 2d canvas.</p>\n<p>For example if a player cannot see a token in the 2d canvas they will not see it in the 3d canvas as well.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>If some of your tokens are terrain components, remember to enable the \"Always visible\" option and to disable \"Draggable\" once you are done placing them.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>If you want Fog of War you can enable the experimental setting in the Scene Configuration</p>","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Cspu3pxFr7tu7SU7":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.OSIqivwFe0qrJF26"}}}
{"_id":"Jsm8aknck1CZcEz4","name":"Loading Models / Token Configuration","content":"<h1>Loading Models</h1>\n<p> </p>\n<p>All models are loaded through tokens in the 3D tab</p>\n<p>Generally a loded model will \"just work\" and be scaled to the size of the token</p>\n<p>If the rotation is incorrect, 99% of the times you can fix it by setting an X Rotation of 270 degrees</p>\n<p> </p>\n<h2>Supported Formats</h2>\n<p> </p>\n<p>You can use <strong>glb</strong>, <strong>gltf </strong>and <strong>fbx </strong>files, other formats can be easly converted</p>\n<p> </p>\n<h2>Token Config</h2>\n<p> </p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>3D Model</strong>: This is the 3d model you want to load, FBX, GLB and GLTF files are supported - if your file is in a different format check resources(3d).md for the conversion process (it's pretty easy)</li>\n<li><strong>Texture</strong>: This is the texture applied to the 3d model, if no model is present in the 3D Model field this image will be used as a \"stand up\" 2d image. animated formats are supported</li>\n<li><strong>Material</strong>: You can change how the material of the model looks, keep in mind that this is supported only for simple models. When using standups it's suggested to use the Basic material so they don't get darkened by shadows. The Texture/Color option will preserve the original model data while modifing only those two parameters (this is suggested for 3d models included in the 3D Canvas Compendium)</li>\n<li><strong>Color</strong>: This is the color to use for the model, this will also colorize \"stand up\" images</li>\n<li><strong>Draggable:</strong> Whether to enable or not mouse interaction, usefull for scenery models that you don't want to drag around during gameplay</li>\n<li><strong>Always Visible</strong>: Since tokens in the 3d view follow vision rules from the 2d view - you can force certain models to always be visible (usually scenery/props)</li>\n<li><strong>Animation Index</strong>: If the model has multiple animations you can chose which one to use - keep in mind that you can use macros to change this number and it will be updated live in the 3d canvas.</li>\n<li><strong>Offeset parameters</strong>: Rotation and Offset parameters are usefull to move your model, usually this won't be necessary and you will be at moste setting the Rotation X to 270 for converted STLs but you have the option. Scale is scale :P.</li>\n<li><strong>Collision Plane</strong>: If enabled this model will be used for collision calculation when dragging. Keep in mind that complex models might not work.</li>\n</ul>","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Cspu3pxFr7tu7SU7":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.km2jLZIdSdtzzPtQ"}}}
{"_id":"OKVEtpGWSYv3qKpR","name":"Known Issues and Limitations","content":"<h1>Transparency</h1>\n<p> </p>\n<p>This is probably the main limitation you will encounter. When stacking multiple images that have transparency, webgl will simply fail to render them correctly. You will notice objects rendered in the incorrect order.</p>\n<p>Unfortunatelly there is no way to avoid this, but here are some tips.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>If you have a map with a lot of tiles with transparency, DO NOT use standup tokens, use 3D models instead</li>\n<li>If your transparent images are limited to standup tokens you will generally be fine</li>\n<li>If you use just standup tokens, consider using 3d models for your maps.</li>\n</ul>\n<p> </p>\n<h2>Updated</h2>\n<p>I'm leaving the previous information for posterity, but now transparency will work fine. but... There is a catch</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p><strong>The catch</strong>: Instead of actually rendering transparency i'm discarding pixel that are semitransparent, so if your transparent image has a fade to transparent effect it will be abruptly cut off, still i think that this is better than the previous implementation.</p>","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Cspu3pxFr7tu7SU7":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.iAZAVAWQee66v85b"}}}
{"_id":"PefJskC7QU90pQtA","name":"Resources","content":"<h2>3D Canvas Compendium</h2>\n<p>This module includes some premade maps and tokens, the list of 3d tokens is continuously updated you can get it <a href=\"https://github.com/theripper93/canvas3dcompendium\">HERE</a></p>\n<p> </p>\n<h2>Terrains:</h2>\n<p> </p>\n<p>You can find plenty of free terrains here: <a href=\"https://sketchfab.com/search?q=tag%3Aterrain&amp;sort_by=-likeCount&amp;type=models\">https://sketchfab.com/search?q=tag%3Aterrain&amp;sort_by=-likeCount&amp;type=models</a></p>\n<p> </p>\n<h2>3D Models:</h2>\n<p> </p>\n<p>This guy has alot of good stuff, needs conversion to gltf: <a href=\"https://quaternius.com/index.html\">https://quaternius.com/index.html</a></p>\n<p>Free miniatures (requires account, stuff is paid but it's only for the 3d print, the model is free): <a href=\"https://www.shapeways.com/shops/dmworkshop\">https://www.shapeways.com/shops/dmworkshop</a></p>\n<p>How to convert STLs: <a href=\"https://youtu.be/2UwQ5v1uQy0\">https://youtu.be/2UwQ5v1uQy0</a></p>\n<p> </p>\n<h2>Skyboxes:</h2>\n<p> </p>\n<p>Skyboxes by Zachery “skiingpenguins” Slocum: <a href=\"https://opengameart.org/content/skiingpenguins-skybox-pack\">https://opengameart.org/content/skiingpenguins-skybox-pack</a></p>\n<p> </p>\n<h2>Utility</h2>\n<p> </p>\n<p>Model Converter: <a href=\"https://products.aspose.app/3d/conversion/fbx-to-gltf\">https://products.aspose.app/3d/conversion/fbx-to-gltf</a></p>\n<p>Model Editor: <a href=\"https://threejs.org/editor/\">https://threejs.org/editor/</a></p>\n<p> </p>\n<h2>Other:</h2>\n<p> </p>\n<p>Sketchfab has tons of free 3d assets that you can download already in the correct format: <a href=\"https://sketchfab.com/\">https://sketchfab.com/</a></p>","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Cspu3pxFr7tu7SU7":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.h4tPTGJHnM44exoo"}}}
{"_id":"X2NSgvN8UN8w8yNm","name":"Video Tutorials","content":"<h1>Video Tutorials</h1>\n<h2>Full tutorial and feature showcase: </h2>\n<h2><iframe title=\"YouTube video player\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/C5Fv8uU0tkc\" width=\"560\" height=\"315\"></iframe></h2>\n<h2>FAQ</h2>\n<h2> <iframe title=\"YouTube video player\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/-eu-zTtRnLQ\" width=\"560\" height=\"315\"></iframe></h2>\n<h2>Converting STLs</h2>\n<h2><iframe title=\"YouTube video player\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/j8sZ-VM0FoI\" width=\"560\" height=\"315\"></iframe></h2>\n<h2>3Dfy 2D Maps</h2>\n<h2><iframe title=\"YouTube video player\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/n6FVHp3wr0I\" width=\"560\" height=\"315\"></iframe></h2>\n<h2>Fast 3D Maps using Blender Asset Library (by Lucas Ferreira)</h2>\n<h2 style=\"position:relative;padding-bottom:56.25%;height:0\"><iframe style=\"position:absolute;top:0;left:0;width:100%;height:100%\" src=\"https://www.loom.com/embed/af605e3960ff487c89a5c0a8f28c6a71\"></iframe></h2>\n<p> </p>","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Cspu3pxFr7tu7SU7":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.lDYHSBnuNxuLGGeH"}}}
{"_id":"afBmgca8XsnQady0","name":"Tiles","content":"<h1>Tiles</h1>\n<p> </p>\n<p>Tiles are rendered at the bottom elevation set through the Levels module. While background tiles are rendered as well it's highly suggested that you instead use a single background image or you will have popping and zindexing issues. The module DF Architect has an option to bake all your background tiles into the background image itself.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<h2>Monk's Active Tile Triggers</h2>\n<p>3D Canvas supports MATT click and double click events on tiles</p>","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Cspu3pxFr7tu7SU7":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.4UlW6pbiHyThOk8n"}}}
{"_id":"tNhh3h8lxInr4ObC","name":"Module Settings","content":"<h1>Module Settings</h1>\n<p> </p>\n<p>The module settings will give you (and your players) a lot of performance options as well as some other stuff. All this options have hints on what they do, you can check them out in the module settings!</p>\n<p> </p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Selection Highlight image</strong>: This image will replace the default ugly squares that are used if no image is provided, this image will show whenever a token is selected or highlighted. I suggest using any of the turn marker indicators (for example from Combat Booster) animated assets are not supported. The module includes one by default, and an extra one with a driectional indicator arrow.</li>\n<li><strong>Stand-ups face camera</strong>: When using tokens in standup mode (aka a 2d image that stands up) this option will determine if those tokens always face the camera</li>\n<li><strong>Prevent negative elevations</strong>: if enabled will prevent drag movement to go below the grid when changing elevation</li>\n<li><strong>Enable Canvas Popout</strong>: If enabled will automatically open the 2d canvas in a separate window when the 3d mode is engaged. Keep in mind that you can always open\\toggle the canvas popout with the button under the cube button to enable the 3d mode</li>\n<li><strong>Disable light/shadows</strong>: This is a perormance option that will massively boost framerate on lower end hardware - all dynamic lighting will be disabled and only a global light will be left</li>\n<li><strong>Resolution</strong>: High (full resolution), Medium (half resolution), Low (quarter resolution)</li>\n</ul>","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Cspu3pxFr7tu7SU7":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.uQHf9V42pg5WP6V4"}}}
